data.title: What shows should Qubo acquire?
data.meta_description:
IKR? What a waste. They air it for several months and then dump it out.
It's like wasting food for nothing.
data.text:

No way... the Noggin app was launched on my birthday... I didn't know that.

Seeing as how Mysticons got dumped by Nickelodeon recently, I wouldn't be surprised if that got picked up by Qubo in a few years. I also expect Sabrina: The Animated Series to air.

I thought of some shows, which are not necessarily owned by Qubo's distributors, but that doesn't mean that Qubo couldn't possibly get other shows from other distributors:

Sagwa, the Chinese Siamese Cat (this one hasn't aired on PBS in YEARS and I researched and it's now owned by a company called HG Distribution in Canada)

Dragon Tales (Dragon Tales' distribution is handled by Sony, I think?)

Harold and the Purple Crayon (The HBO Family series that Sony owns.)

The Big Comfy Couch (Nobody's aired it in the US in years and it would be nice to see again.)

Franklin

Little Bear

While on the topic of 9Story here’s some shows they recently acquired that could come to Qubo:

Goosebumps

Astroblast

Maya and Miguel (my local PBS station still airs it though)

WordGirl (same as above)

The Babysitters Club

Again maybe...
